[Measles in the UK has been linked to summer festivals. See: ProMED-mail. Measles update (49): UK (S. Wales) summer festivals, Romania 20160925.4513493. But this is only because the level of herd immunity required to keep measles in check has not been maintained. The best means of containment of measles is the maintenance of high initial levels of measles immunity in the population through vaccination. Which begs the question, how best to convince antivaccinationists of the need for vaccination. Education is the key, and perhaps the rapid dissemination of information on the spread of measles in the absence of vaccination through such organizations as ProMED-mail may facilitate appreciation of the need for vaccination and the safety of vaccines.

